HEADWORD: Araneous
<hw>A*ra"ne*ous</hw> <pr>(⟦adot⟧*r⟦amac⟧`n⟦esl⟧*⟦ucr⟧s)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>araneosus</ets>, fr. <ets>aranea</ets>
spider, spider's web.]</ety> <def>Cobweblike; extremely thin and
delicate, like a cobweb; <as>as, the <ex>araneous</ex> membrane of the
eye</as>. See <er>Arachnoid</er>.</def> <rj><au>Derham.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
